(firstQuint)The Effect of Whey Protein on Short-Term Food Intake and Post-Meal Blood Glucose Response in Young Men.

 A randomized, cross-over design study was conducted.

 Whey protein preloads (10-40 g) were provided in 300 ml water.

 At 30 min following consumption, subjects were fed an ad libitum pizza meal.

 Satiety, and blood glucose were measured at baseline and selected intervals pre- (0, 15 and 30 min) and post-meal (50, 65, 80 and 95 min).

